###############################################################################
### 🧪 TESTING SCENARIOS
###############################################################################

### Test Error Cases

# Invalid School ID
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/teachers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "first_name": "Test",
  "last_name": "Teacher",
  "email": "test.teacher@archimedesschool.edu",
  "school_id": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"
}

###

# Duplicate Email
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/teachers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "first_name": "Duplicate",
  "last_name": "Teacher",
  "email": "sarah.johnson@archimedesschool.edu",
  "school_id": "{{schoolId}}"
}

###

# Invalid Teacher ID
GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/teachers/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

###

# Invalid Pagination
GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/teachers
    ?page=0
    &size=200

###############################################################################
### 📝 NOTES
###############################################################################

# Teacher Management Features:
# ✅ Create teacher with school association
# ✅ Auto-create default courses (based on max_classes setting)
# ✅ Each course gets unique join code for student enrollment
# ✅ Get teacher by ID with school relationship
# ✅ Get paginated teachers with filtering
# ✅ Update teacher information (full or partial)
# ✅ Delete teacher
# ✅ Proper error handling and validation
# ✅ Email and username uniqueness constraints
# ✅ Computed full_name field

# Remember to:
# 1. Create a school first (use schools.http)
# 2. Replace {{schoolId}} with actual school ID
# 3. Replace {{teacherId}} with actual teacher ID from responses
# 4. Use proper pagination (page >= 1, size <= 100)